creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of Short Poetry Collection 133 by Various.
Read in English by SuperCoconut; Glenn O'Brien; Arup Sen; Peter Deligdisch; Andrew K Waugh; Son of the Exiles; Malcolm Fisher; Algy Pug; Bruce Kachuk; Shakira Searle; Willy; inflected; Fiddlesticks; Eunah Choi; Christopher Earnings; Phil Schempf; Ruth Golding

This is a collection of 27 poems read by LibriVox volunteers for June 2014.

This collection includes the following:
All Things Bright and Beautiful, by Cecil F. Alexander
A Bush Christening, by Andrew Barton "Banjo" Paterson
The City in the Sea, by Edgar Allan Poe
Come Into the Garden, Maud, by Alfred, Lord Tennyson
The Dying Stockman, by Unknown (possibly A.B. 'Banjo' Patterson)
Faces in the Street, by Henry Lawson
Gunga Din, by Rudyard Kipling
Hymn to Love, by Lascelles Abercrombie
Josef Hofmann, by Elizabeth Porter Gould
The Last of His Tribe, by Henry C. Kendall
Sonnet I (Love, though for this you riddle me with darts), by Edna St. Vincent Millay
The Old Man's Grave, by Lucy Maud Montgomery
One Way of Love, by Robert Browning
On Lake Memphremagog, by Elizabeth Porter Gould
The Penitent, by Edna St. Vincent Millay
The Pilgrim's Wants, by Anonymous
Presence of Love, by Samuel Taylor Coleridge
Richard Cory, by Edwin Arlington Robinson
The Seafarer: a Translation from Old English Lyric, by Lola LaMotte Iddings
Sea Sand, by Sara Teasdale
A Smuggler's Song, by Rudyard Kipling
A Song in Storm, by Rudyard Kipling
Sonnet 18, by William Shakespeare
Sonnet 105, by William Shakespeare
The Sword of Pain, by George Essex Evans
Twinkle Twinkle Little Star, by Anonymous
What Do You Care?, by William Edward Ross

For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
